John J. COX, Appellant, v. The MICHIGAMME OIL COMPANY, a Michigan Corporation, Alleged Bankrupt, and Edna E. House Rogers, Appellees. No. 7905. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Dec. 16, 1937. John W. Conlin and Frank B. Devine, both of Ann Arbor, Mich., for appellant. Arch D. Wilson, of Ann Arbor, Mich., for appellees.

Before HICKS arid SIMONS, Circuit Judges, and RAYMOND, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the motion of appellee, Edna E. House Rogers, to dismiss the appeal herein be, and the same is, sustained, and the appeal is hereby dismissed.
